description:
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Senior Sister / Ward Manager Stroke and Neuro-rehabilitation &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;An exciting opportunity has come up to work in the Neuro and Stroke Rehabilitation ward as a Senior Sister on Thomas Young Ward St. George&#39;s University Hospitals NHS Foundation Trust. We are looking for an inspiring, self-motivated individual to join us and develop this senior leadership role in neuro-rehab/Stroke.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Thomas Young Ward specialises in high quality care of 10 neuro rehabilitation patients and 16 Stroke rehabilitation patients. Separate multi-disciplinary teams are responsible for rehabilitation and care of these groups of patients.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Our specialty makes us exciting, ambitious and forward-thinking. Our candidates need to be visionary, highly competent change innovators and, most of all, have vision to transform rehabilitation nursing supported by the skills, knowledge and experience to deliver the change&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We are looking for a forward thinking professional role model who is an enthusiastic and innovative practitioner, able to lead and motivate the nursing staff in the provision of high quality, patient focused nursing care.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;As part of this team, you will inspire the nursing team, leading, coaching, managing and role- modeling in Interdisciplinary working environment.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Requirements&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Minimum of 2 years at band 6 within Neurosciences&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Excellent leadership and communication skills&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Catherine Chambers Matron for Neuro Rehabilitation via email Catherine.Chambers@stgeorges.nhs.uk&lt;/p&gt;
